    "comments" : [
      {
        "id" : "e69cc2eb-06eb-4231-a13d-1334186ccce8",
        "parentId" : null,
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "Probably should add `numpy` explicitly too.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T15:31:30Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T15:51:53Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "770c5609-2b96-4813-b327-072f9a605460",
        "parentId" : "e69cc2eb-06eb-4231-a13d-1334186ccce8",
        "authorId" : "04999101-b7b8-41ec-b9d1-f9411615a75c",
        "body" : "Usually `bob` packages link against `bob.blitz` and `bob.math` and not against `numpy` directly. I don't see any direct usage of `numpy` here:(https://github.com/bioidiap/bob.ap/search?l=cpp&q=numpy&utf8=%E2%9C%93)\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T15:40:29Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T15:51:53Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "04999101-b7b8-41ec-b9d1-f9411615a75c",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "f327367a-67b5-4885-83c8-ca1d70d1577a",
        "parentId" : "e69cc2eb-06eb-4231-a13d-1334186ccce8",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "So, adding `numpy` doesn't mean we are linking against it. Only adding `numpy x.x` does. However, as `scipy` is present, we know `numpy` is a dependency. So it is nice to add here to be explicit. Especially if linkages are added in the future.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T15:44:30Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T15:51:53Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "756bbf3f-6a06-4d97-aeca-7ff77eed4915",
        "parentId" : "e69cc2eb-06eb-4231-a13d-1334186ccce8",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "I guess I am still unsure as `bob.blitz` is linking against NumPy. As long as `bob.blitz` is not exposing any NumPy C API or ABI as part of its interface or changing its interface based on NumPy, this should be ok. If you run into issues, just add the `x.x`, bump the build number, and re-render the feedstock with `conda-smithy`.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T16:36:32Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T16:36:32Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      }
    ],
    "commit" : "35a6ae9614ecb497543e034d96f8002fa3a8343c",
    "line" : null,
