        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "Are we using Fortran or C++0x/C++11 here?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T15:32:09Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T15:51:53Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "a5f23546-a39b-4e69-9ff3-c0f5c9fcc029",
        "parentId" : "92c1ca05-c498-45ae-a5e6-4dc9d1b7b80a",
        "authorId" : "04999101-b7b8-41ec-b9d1-f9411615a75c",
        "body" : "`C++0x` yes. It is added to compile flags by `bob.extension`.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T15:42:03Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T15:51:53Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "04999101-b7b8-41ec-b9d1-f9411615a75c",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "6885ba8d-9468-4541-8ce8-b34f46e9932e",
        "parentId" : "92c1ca05-c498-45ae-a5e6-4dc9d1b7b80a",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "Thanks for confirming.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-14T15:47:14Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-14T15:51:53Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "f8fa0921-ec1a-49d4-aacd-a4632e3243fd",
        "parentId" : "92c1ca05-c498-45ae-a5e6-4dc9d1b7b80a",
        "authorId" : "66a942d9-0cdd-4a44-9306-e21989fcca81",
        "body" : "In this package, we're including a header from bob.sp which declares `fftpack.h`, the C interface for a FORTRAN subroutine. We're linking against the fortran binaries, but using a C API for that.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-15T07:58:38Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-15T07:58:38Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "66a942d9-0cdd-4a44-9306-e21989fcca81",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "b98950e9-cef7-4b27-80ac-9155ffecfdf1",
        "parentId" : "92c1ca05-c498-45ae-a5e6-4dc9d1b7b80a",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "So, C++0x is not needed then?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-15T12:07:09Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-15T12:07:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "7e7e1872-b237-458c-a37f-c7e97f0069f6",
        "parentId" : "92c1ca05-c498-45ae-a5e6-4dc9d1b7b80a",
        "authorId" : "66a942d9-0cdd-4a44-9306-e21989fcca81",
        "body" : "C++0x is always required in bob.\\* packages with bindings.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-15T12:18:34Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-15T12:18:34Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "66a942d9-0cdd-4a44-9306-e21989fcca81",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "dd51cfe5-de7d-4fdc-b97c-65da15fc6982",
        "parentId" : "92c1ca05-c498-45ae-a5e6-4dc9d1b7b80a",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "Ok, then it is fine. The main point here is we try not to use the `gcc` package unless it is strictly required. So, if we required newer C++ features or we need a Fortran compiler or similar.\n\nWe have several proposals that may eliminate this package on Linux in the future, but it is a pretty controversial and complex topic so it may be a while before we get there.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-04-15T12:33:00Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-04-15T12:33:00Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      }
